2022. I think you’re one of those years I won’t appreciate fully until your further in the rearview. Here’s to weddings and best friends and getting tipsy at a luau. Here’s to snowy Christmas’s and horse riding and recording an album. Here’s to the highs (and the lows) of life that keep me grounded, grateful and hungry for whatever’s next. ✌️💕 #2022 #2022recap #newyear #life

10 Things I learned in 2022

1. You never regret taking the trip ( even if it’s an 11 hour travel day for a couple of nights drunk in Hawaii with your best friends ) 
2. Always show your hair stylist a photo of what you want, or risk getting what you don’t want
3. Having real flowers and not just fake ones in your house is actually pretty lovely
4. If you put enough hours in, you will eventually not hate your own demos in the car
5. I think Bae Juice actually works. 
6. Euphoria should not be watched on an airplane, next to a stranger (so many dicks!)
7. Riding bikes is actually fun WHO KNEW
8. Pink does in fact have a lot of bangers, enough for a ‘best of’ burned cd that gets a road trip going
9. Leeches can climb remarkably fast without legs 
10. There is magic found in missed flights, in bad showboats and even in the no’s you don’t wanna hear.

Fantasy Island is for all the exaggerated love stories in my mind, with sometimes very real protagonists. 

It’s for the kind of heartbreak that overstays it’s welcome and the kind of love I thought only existed in the make believe, but I found out was even better than the books. Pre-save Fantasy Island now (link in bio) less than a week away 💙 #words #trailer

Fantasy Island is blue skies and big open pastures.

It’s daydreams set in daisy fields and making wishes on dandelions and in old wells, knowing some won’t come true. 

It’s big feelings in pretty dresses and saying what you really wanted to say in the moment. 

Fantasy Island is out everywhere this week. (Pre-save link in bio) #words #newmusic #daydream

Fantasy Island is getting the kind of lost, in your imagination, that makes you feel found…again. 

Out everywhere this week 💙 pre-save link in bio

Welcome to Fantasy Island. 

It’s for you to get lost in. 

It’s for the daydreamer in me who still believes that life at its very core is more magic than tragedy and that even the worst parts can paint some beautiful portraits. 

I hope you come into my world for a moment and come out a little covered in glitter.

Fantasy Island. I am so proud of this album & I couldn’t have done it without a plethora of talented people who I adore. To my producers on this album, it has been really special making this with you. To my team at empire who had to deal with my sporadic, often caffeine induced ideas about everything, you guys helped bring this to life. To the musicians who played on this and the mix and mastering engineers, I’m so grateful for all of you putting your time, energy and talent into this. And to YOU, wherever you are in the world, for putting this on in your headphones or in your car. For sending it to a friend or learning the lyrics. That has long been my fantasy. Thank you for coming into my world and letting me be part of your life. 💙 listen to Fantasy Island everywhere now (link in bio)

February 11 in 2022. I had built a track on logic a couple days prior & I was playing around with a topline, honestly it came pretty quick because I’d had the lyric idea for Land Speed Records in my phone for a minute (from whenever the Olympics were lol) I had this little demo & it was all of my friends favourite song, they would call me when they were drinking scream singing it so I guess I took that as a sign. I sent the demo to @aaronwagner.co and we went in to cut it for real and he made it into the pop song of my dreams! I love the journey a song goes on. Listen to how it turned out (link in bio) #originstory #storybehindthesong #songwriting

July 11 , 2022. Me playing my keytar (terribly might I add) and trying to figure out this little idea I had called ‘Let The Record Show’ it was an idea I had written in my phone on a long dive with Ben, feeling very peaceful. I ended up figuring out the chorus idea when I swapped over to guitar 😅 and knew it was the last song of the album. I brought it in for my session with @nobysidez & the vocal you hear on the record is from that first day cutting it 🥰 listen to how it turned out (link in bio) #originstories #thestorybehindthesong #songideas #voicememos

March 18, 2022. My twin sister @desireetaylor was in town and we had a co-write with @nedcameron scheduled for later that day so we were messing around with an idea on guitar. Tbh Dez came up with a lot of lyrics that I thought were even too scathing to add 😂 The bones were there but the song became a real drinking song when we finished it with Ned. This was one of my favourite songs to write/cut for the album because it’s.just.so.FUN! @desireetaylor also wrote a song with me on my first album (Surprised) so now it’s officially a tradition and I will co-write a song with her on every album 💙 listen to how it turned out (link in bio) #originstory #songwriting #acousticversion #storybehindthesong

summer dump 🌞

Own Roses is almost at 2 million streams. This might not be a big deal to some people, but it’s a big deal to me. When I wrote this song by myself on a piano, it was the lifeboat I so desperately needed and the past couple years I’ve somehow needed it even more, a reminder that growth can be incredibly messy and ugly and painful. But that if you’re lucky, you’ll come out on the other side a better version of you. I wanted to make a new little video to it that shows life as it so often is; sad, happy, gut wrenching, fun and full of feelings that at times feel really hard to appreciate the weight of. And for anyone going through a hard season of life, you are blooming and you will get the garden you deserve. Here’s to the downpours…and the roses. I love you for listening 🌹♥️ #growth #ownroses #originalsong
